SUNDAY EVENING AN AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN SEA
1030 EXTENDING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS ICELAND AND SCANDINAVIA. A
LOW PRESSURE LIES ACROSS SEA AREA SHANNON WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE AROUND 984
WITH A CYCLONIC PATTERN DOMINATING WERN UK SEA AREAS. PRESSURE WILL REMAIN
HIGH ACROSS SCANDINAVIA AND ICELAND THROUGHOUT ALTHOUGH THE HIGH WILL DECLINE
SLTLY THROUGH THE PERIOD TO AROUND 1020. THE LOW PRESSURE WILL GRADUALLY
FILL IN SITU DURING MONDAY TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY REACHING A CENTRAL PRESSURE
OF 998 BY WEDNESDAY. SUNDAY EVENING INTO MONDAY GALES AND NEAR GALES ARE
EXP FOR FASTNET SHANNON AND ROCKALL WITH STRG WINDS AFFECTING ALL PORTPATRICK
SEA AREAS. WIND STRENGTH WILL DECREASE GRADUALLY THROUGH THE PERIOD WITH
NO NEAR GALES OR GALES EXP BY LATE WEDNESDAY AND STRG WINDS RESTRICTED TO
THE FAR N AND S OF PORTPATRICK
